  "prompt": "How is the square root of 50 simplified?",
  "response": "To simplify the square root of 50, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Factorize 50 into its prime factors:**\n   \n   \\[\n   50 = 2 \\times 25\n   \\]\n   \n   \\[\n   25 = 5 \\times 5\n   \\]\n   \n   So, \n   \n   \\[\n   50 = 2 \\times 5 \\times 5\n   \\]\n\n2. **Express the square root using the prime factors:**\n   \n   \\[\n   \\sqrt{50} = \\sqrt{2 \\times 5 \\times 5}\n   \\]\n\n3. **Simplify the square root by taking out pairs of identical factors:**\n   \n   \\[\n   \\sqrt{2 \\times 5 \\times 5} = 5 \\times \\sqrt{2}\n   \\]\n\n4. **Write the simplified form:**\n   \n   \\[\n   \\sqrt{50} = 5\\sqrt{2}\n   \\]\n\n**Final Answer:**\n\n\\[\n\\boxed{5\\sqrt{2}}\n\\]",
